# Hono Documentation

Use current Hono docs — do not rely on training data for API details.

## Priority 1: Hono MCP server

If the `hono` MCP server is available, use these tools:

1. `search_hono_docs` — find pages by keyword; filter with `category` (`getting-started`, `middleware`, `helpers`, `guides`, `concepts`, `api`)
2. `fetch_hono_doc` — get full Markdown by URL or slug
3. `list_hono_topics` — browse all indexed topics

Workflow: search first, then fetch the most relevant page.

## Priority 2: Context7 MCP (fallback)

If the Hono MCP server is unavailable, use Context7 `resolve-library-id` then `query-docs`:

| Source | Preferred Context7 library ID |
| --- | --- |
| Hono docs site | `/websites/hono_dev` |
| Hono website repo | `/honojs/website` |
| Hono source | `/honojs/hono` |
| LLMs full index | `/llmstxt/hono_dev_llms-full_txt` |

Pass the user's full question as the `query` parameter.

## Priority 3: Direct sources (shell fallback)

```bash
# Doc index
curl -s https://hono.dev/llms.txt

# Full/tiny doc dumps
curl -s https://hono.dev/llms-full.txt
curl -s https://hono.dev/llms-small.txt

# Fetch a page as Markdown
curl -sH "Accept: text/markdown" https://hono.dev/docs/getting-started/cloudflare-workers
curl -sH "Accept: text/markdown" https://hono.dev/docs/api/hono
curl -sH "Accept: text/markdown" https://hono.dev/docs/middleware/builtin/jwt
```

